questiontext.text: Approximately 10.3% of American high school students drop out of school before graduation. Choose 10 students entering high school at random. Find the probability that no more than 2 drop out.
Approximately 10.3% of American high school students drop out of school before graduation. Choose 10 students entering high school at random. Find the probability that at least 6 graduate.

Approximately 10.3% of American high school students drop out of school before graduation. Choose 10 students entering high school at random. Find the probability that all 10 stay in school and graduate.
A survey found that 10% of Americans believe that they have seen a UFO. For a sample of 10 people, find the probability that at least 2 believe they have seen a UFO.
A survey found that 10% of Americans believe that they have seen a UFO. For a sample of 10 people, find the probability that 2 or 3 believe they have seen a UFO.
A survey found that 10% of Americans believe that they have seen a UFO. For a sample of 10 people, find the probability that exactly 1 believes they have seen a UFO.
A student takes a 20-question, multiple choice exam with five choices for each question. Find the probability of guessing correctly on at least half of the questions.
Twenty percent of Americans ages 25 to 74 have high blood pressure. If 16 randomly selected Americans ages 25 to 74 are selected, find the probability that none will have high blood pressure.
Twenty percent of Americans ages 25 to 74 have high blood pressure. If 16 randomly selected Americans ages 25 to 74 are selected, find the probability that half will have high blood pressure.
Twenty percent of Americans ages 25 to 74 have high blood pressure. If 16 randomly selected Americans ages 25 to 74 are selected, find the probability that exactly 4 will have high blood pressure.

It has been reported that 83% of federal government employees use email. If a sample of 200 federal government employees is selected, how many of them would you expect to not use email?
